SIAP is the data set that contains information for 299 crops accross Mexico during the time period from 1980 to 2016.

SIAP <- read.csv("SIAP.csv")

Subset the SIAP data set to extract the data for perennials:

perennials <- SIAP %>% 
  filter(cycle == "perennial" & type == "food") %>%
  #group_by(state, crop, year) %>% 
  group_by(state, crop, year) %>% 
  summarise(sum(production), sum(losses)) 
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'state', 'crop' (override with `.groups` argument)
perennials_v2 <- SIAP %>% 
  select()

#colnames(perennials) <- c("state", "crop", "year", "production")
colnames(perennials) <- c("state","crop", "year", "production", "losses")
tmp <- gather(perennials, "production", "losses", 3:4)
colnames(tmp) <- c("crop", "year", "variable", "value")

perennials %>% 
  DT::datatable()

Distribution

olives <- perennials %>% 
  filter(crop == "aceituna")

gg_miss_fct(olives, state)

ggplot(olives, aes(x=state, y=production)) + geom_boxplot() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 0.5, vjust = 0.5))
